The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks and their vulnerability to adversarial perturbations, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on identifying safe regions of the input space using clustering and verification techniques suggests a strong connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for computer vision (cs.CV) and bio-informatics also indicates a potential fit for those sub-categories. Additionally, the concern for safety and security aligns with the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR), while the evaluation of a neural network implementation for unmanned aircraft suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
